<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="386" pageId="4" pageNumber="385" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1261,1576]" pageId="4" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1261,1287]" pageId="4" pageNumber="385">Description.</emphasis>
Green or pale green (
<figureCitation box="[552,690,1261,1288]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–28" captionStartId="10.[151,264,2000,2024]" captionTargetBox="[162,1424,185,1973]" captionTargetId="figure-25@10.[158,1430,181,1976]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 5–28. Macropsis spp., lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4404165/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="385">Figs. 11–16</figureCitation>
). Forewings hyaline or slightly infumose, darkest in apical parts. Dorsal part of abdomen usually more or less darkened, black abdominal terga visible through forewings. Ends of tarsi often darkened. In males dark coloration is more developed than in females.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1261,1576]" pageId="4" pageNumber="385">
Abdominal apodemes of 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[493,509,1369,1383]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="385">nd</superScript>
tergite in male short, separated by broad notch (
<figureCitation box="[1043,1220,1369,1395]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–81" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[183,1402,189,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-16@15.[173,1413,181,1869]" captionText="FIGURES 48–81. Macropsis suspecta (48–54), M. vicina (55–61), M. tarbagataica (62–68), and M. iliensis (69–81). 48–49, 55–56, 62–63―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 50–51, 57–58, 64–65, 69, 71—the 2nd sternite; 52–53, 59–60, 66–67, 70, 72, 74, 77, 80―penis, lateral view; 54, 61, 68, 75, 78, 81―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 73, 76, 79―male 2nd abdominal apodemes. 69–70―paratype of M. iliensis; 71–72―paratype of M. tuvensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457944" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457944/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="385">Figs. 73, 76, 79</figureCitation>
). Sternal apodemes strongly convergent, with wide bases and slightly expanded tips sometimes almost touching each other and separated by narrow gap (
<figureCitation box="[393,658,1441,1467]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–81" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[183,1402,189,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-16@15.[173,1413,181,1869]" captionText="FIGURES 48–81. Macropsis suspecta (48–54), M. vicina (55–61), M. tarbagataica (62–68), and M. iliensis (69–81). 48–49, 55–56, 62–63―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 50–51, 57–58, 64–65, 69, 71—the 2nd sternite; 52–53, 59–60, 66–67, 70, 72, 74, 77, 80―penis, lateral view; 54, 61, 68, 75, 78, 81―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 73, 76, 79―male 2nd abdominal apodemes. 69–70―paratype of M. iliensis; 71–72―paratype of M. tuvensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457944" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457944/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="385">Figs. 69, 71, 73, 76, 79</figureCitation>
). Penis in side view wide, with only slight if any extension in middle (
<figureCitation box="[159,423,1477,1504]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–81" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[183,1402,189,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-16@15.[173,1413,181,1869]" captionText="FIGURES 48–81. Macropsis suspecta (48–54), M. vicina (55–61), M. tarbagataica (62–68), and M. iliensis (69–81). 48–49, 55–56, 62–63―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 50–51, 57–58, 64–65, 69, 71—the 2nd sternite; 52–53, 59–60, 66–67, 70, 72, 74, 77, 80―penis, lateral view; 54, 61, 68, 75, 78, 81―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 73, 76, 79―male 2nd abdominal apodemes. 69–70―paratype of M. iliensis; 71–72―paratype of M. tuvensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457944" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457944/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="385">Figs. 70, 72, 74, 77, 80</figureCitation>
). 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[456,472,1477,1491]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="385">nd</superScript>
valvulae of ovipositor with 3–4 preapical teeth (
<figureCitation box="[1017,1196,1477,1504]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–81" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[183,1402,189,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-16@15.[173,1413,181,1869]" captionText="FIGURES 48–81. Macropsis suspecta (48–54), M. vicina (55–61), M. tarbagataica (62–68), and M. iliensis (69–81). 48–49, 55–56, 62–63―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 50–51, 57–58, 64–65, 69, 71—the 2nd sternite; 52–53, 59–60, 66–67, 70, 72, 74, 77, 80―penis, lateral view; 54, 61, 68, 75, 78, 81―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 73, 76, 79―male 2nd abdominal apodemes. 69–70―paratype of M. iliensis; 71–72―paratype of M. tuvensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457944" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457944/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="385">Figs. 75, 78, 81</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
