<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">
Specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[396,527,727,753]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[542,676,727,753]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, Tyva, and 
<collectingCountry box="[814,923,727,753]" name="Mongolia" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
are similar in shape of male apodemes and genitalia and in a number of preapical teeth on 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[695,711,762,776]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">nd</superScript>
valvulae of ovipositor (
<figureCitation box="[980,1119,763,790]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–81" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[183,1402,189,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-16@15.[173,1413,181,1869]" captionText="FIGURES 48–81. Macropsis suspecta (48–54), M. vicina (55–61), M. tarbagataica (62–68), and M. iliensis (69–81). 48–49, 55–56, 62–63―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 50–51, 57–58, 64–65, 69, 71—the 2nd sternite; 52–53, 59–60, 66–67, 70, 72, 74, 77, 80―penis, lateral view; 54, 61, 68, 75, 78, 81―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 73, 76, 79―male 2nd abdominal apodemes. 69–70―paratype of M. iliensis; 71–72―paratype of M. tuvensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457944" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457944/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">Figs. 69–81</figureCitation>
). Still, specimens from 
<collectingCountry name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
and Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[398,529,799,825]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
usually have somewhat brighter coloration (
<figureCitation box="[1027,1108,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–28" captionStartId="10.[151,264,2000,2024]" captionTargetBox="[162,1424,185,1973]" captionTargetId="figure-25@10.[158,1430,181,1976]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 5–28. Macropsis spp., lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4404165/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) and/or lighter tarsi tips (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 5–28" captionStartId="10.[151,264,2000,2024]" captionTargetBox="[162,1424,185,1973]" captionTargetId="figure-25@10.[158,1430,181,1976]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 5–28. Macropsis spp., lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4404165/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). However, in males from Southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[629,760,835,861]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
coloration is typical of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vilbaste" authorityYear="1980" box="[1024,1151,835,860]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="386" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuvensis">
<emphasis box="[1024,1151,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">M. tuvensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Tyva and 
<collectingCountry box="[1327,1436,835,861]" name="Mongolia" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,337,870,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–28" captionStartId="10.[151,264,2000,2024]" captionTargetBox="[162,1424,185,1973]" captionTargetId="figure-25@10.[158,1430,181,1976]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 5–28. Macropsis spp., lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4404165/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">Figs. 13 and 15</figureCitation>
), but calling signal pattern is the same as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mityaev" authorityYear="1971" box="[840,957,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="386" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iliensis">
<emphasis box="[840,957,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">M. iliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1027,1102,871,897]" name="Russia" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">Russia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1158,1287,871,897]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
(82–91). For this reason, we establish the synonymy 
<taxonomicName authority="Mityaev, 1971" authorityName="Mityaev" authorityYear="1971" box="[595,880,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="386" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iliensis">
<emphasis box="[595,712,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">M. iliensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mityaev, I. D." box="[719,880,907,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="386" refId="ref14222" refString="Mityaev, I. D. (1971) Cicadinea of Kazakhstan. Keys for identification of species. &quot; Nauka &quot; Publ., Alma-Ata, 211 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1971">Mityaev, 1971</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
= 
<taxonomicName authority="Vilbaste, 1980" authorityName="Vilbaste" authorityYear="1980" box="[910,1209,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="386" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuvensis" status="syn. n.">
<emphasis box="[910,1037,907,932]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">M. tuvensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Vilbaste, Yu. G." box="[1045,1209,907,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="386" refId="ref14993" refString="Vilbaste, Yu. G. (1980) Fauna of Cicadinea of Tuva. &quot; Valgus &quot; Publ., Tallinn, 219 pp. [in Russian with English summary]" type="book" year="1980">Vilbaste, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1220,1298,907,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1220,1298,907,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">syn. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
